    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> wholewheat tortiglioni </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for an initial 10-12 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-red-pesto-and-broccoli-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> Tenderstem broccoli</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-red-pesto-and-broccoli-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-red-pesto-and-broccoli-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your<strong> bacon</strong> <strong>lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crisp</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>bacon</strong> to kitchen paper and set aside</p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-red-pesto-and-broccoli-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the wholewheat tortiglioni has had 10-12 min, add the chopped<strong> Tenderstem broccoli</strong> and cook for a further 2-4 min or until the broccoli is tender and the pasta is cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> </strong>wholewheat tortiglioni\u00a0and\u00a0broccoli, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-red-pesto-and-broccoli-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved bacon pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your\u00a0<strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> sun-dried tomato pesto</strong> and <strong>soft cheese </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding a pinch more<strong> salt</strong> if needed and cook for 1 min or until fully combined<strong> </strong>\u2013\u00a0this is your<strong> creamy red pesto sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-red-pesto-and-broccoli-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add\u00a0the <strong>drained wholewheat tortiglioni</strong>\u00a0and <strong>broccoli\u00a0</strong>to the <strong>creamy red pesto sauce</strong> with a splash of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min or until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-red-pesto-and-broccoli-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> creamy red pesto & broccoli wholewheat tortiglioni</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>crispy bacon</strong>,\u00a0<strong>grated cheddar</strong> and a good grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
